📄 Part 3 – Processing Flow, Workflow Execution and Sending Logic


---

1. Introduction

This section explains how the system processes an event from the moment a user performs an action until data is sent to Connexis.

It covers:

Trigger conditions

Validation logic

Mapping evaluation

Workflow execution (Camunda)

XML and TAR generation

Sending mechanism



---

2. Entry Point – Validate Action

The Track & Trace process starts when the user clicks the “Validate” button.


---

Why Validate is Important

It acts as the main trigger for integration

Not every event is sent to Connexis

Only events that meet specific conditions are processed



---

3. Pre-Processing Conditions

Before executing any logic, the system performs validation checks.


---

Mandatory Conditions

The system proceeds only if:

The transaction is not an update
(is_update = N)

The customer is eligible
(eb_cus_flag = Y)

A valid mapping exists in the mapping table

The status has not already been successfully sent



---

Blocking Condition (Critical)

The system must NOT send data if:

Connexis status = Sending (02)

AND Connexis Transaction ID is NULL



---

Reason

This condition prevents:

Duplicate transaction creation

Inconsistent updates



---

4. Mapping Evaluation

Once validation is successful, the system evaluates the mapping table.


---

Process

1. Read:

Current event status

Action performed (e.g., Validate)



2. Query mapping table:



SELECT * FROM DPW_EXTERNAL_TRACK_TRACE_MAPPING
WHERE STATUS_CST = current_status
AND ACTION = 'VALIDATE';


---

If Mapping Exists

The system retrieves:

Connexis status (STATUS_CXT)

Product code

Transaction type

Sub transaction type



---

If Mapping Does Not Exist

Process stops

No XML is generated



---

5. Camunda Workflow Execution

After mapping is validated, the system triggers a Camunda workflow.


---

Workflow Steps

Step 1: XML Generation

Data is collected from:

Event table

Mapping table

Customer data

Courier data




---

Step 2: TAR File Creation

XML file is generated

Packaged into a .tar file



---

Step 3: Status Update

Event status is updated to: 👉 Ready (01)



---

6. XML Generation Logic

XML is generated dynamically based on system data and mapping rules.


---

Key Rules

Reference ID (ref_id)

Priority:

1. Connexis reference ID


2. MFR reference


3. Event ID




---

Transaction ID (tnx_id)

Included only if available



---

Mapping-Based Fields

Product code

Transaction type

Status codes



---

BO Status Update

Set to Y if Connexis status exists

Otherwise N



---

Date Handling

Current system time + 2 hours (CET)



---

Conditional Fields

Fields are included only if required

Avoid unnecessary data



---

7. TAR File Generation

After XML creation:


---

Process

XML is compressed into a TAR file



---

Naming Convention

<EVENT_ID>.tar


---

Status Update

Stage	Status

After generation	Ready (01)



---

8. Sending Engine

The system automatically processes events that are ready to be sent.


---

Trigger Condition

👉 Events with status = Ready (01)


---

Steps

1. Select event


2. Re-check validation conditions


3. Apply idempotency check


4. Send TAR file to Connexis


5. Update status




---

Status Transition

Before	After

Ready (01)	Sending (02)



---

9. Idempotency Logic (Duplicate Prevention)

Before sending, the system ensures that the same data is not sent multiple times.


---

Rules

Condition	Action

Already ACK	Do not send
Already successfully sent	Do not send
NACK received	Retry allowed
No previous record	Send



---

Importance

Prevents duplicate transactions

Maintains data integrity



---

10. Auto Trigger (Auto IS Flow)


---

Trigger

Event created automatically



---

Conditions

Customer is eligible

Mapping exists for action = AutoIS



---

Action

Automatically triggers:

XML generation

Sending flow




---

11. Courier-Based Trigger


---

Trigger

User saves courier details



---

Action

XML is generated

TAR is sent to Connexis



---

Data Included

Courier partner

Waybill number



---

12. Status Lifecycle

The event goes through multiple statuses during processing.


---

Flow

Initial → Ready (01) → Sending (02) → ACK / NACK


---

Meaning

Status	Description

Ready (01)	Ready to send
Sending (02)	Sent to Connexis
ACK	Successfully processed
NACK	Processing failed



---

13. Error Handling (Sending Phase)


---

If Mapping Missing

Process stops



---

If Conditions Fail

No action triggered



---

If Sending Fails

Event remains pending

Can be retried



